Package jexec

jexec is a main package of JExec library for simplify the execution of shell commands on Java
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Executor
    A interface to be implemented in the executors
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ErrorExecutor
    A subclass of JExecExecutor to implement only onError(Logger logger, Exception exception) onSuccess(Logger logger) and onExecuted(Log log, Exception exception) are implemented in this class but they do nothing
    ExecutedExecutor
    A subclass of JExecExecutor to implement only onExecuted(Log log, Exception exception) onSuccess(Logger logger) and onError(Logger logger, Exception exception) are implemented in this class but they do nothing
    JExec
    Executes commands and saves the output, command, and return value in a Log object
    JExecExecutor
    Is the implementation of Executor() command(), onSuccess(Logger logger), onError(Logger logger, Exception exception), onExecuted(Log log, Exception exception) remain not implemented to allow an external implementation
    Log  
    Logger
    Represents the Logger of multiple commands
    SuccessExecutor
    A subclass of JExecExecutor to implement only onError(Logger logger, Exception exception) onError(Logger logger, Exception exception) and onExecuted(Log log, Exception exception) are implemented in this class but they do nothing
    Utils
    Contains various useful methods
